Success Nwogu, Abuja The Peoples Democratic Party has commenced activities for party congresses in 26 states. The affected states are Abia, Akwa Ibom, Bauchi, Bayelsa, Benue, Cross River, Delta, Ebonyi, Edo, Ekiti, Enugu, Federal Capital Territory, Gombe, Imo, Jigawa, Kaduna, Kano, Katsina, Nasarawa, Niger, Ondo, Plateau, Rivers, Sokoto, Taraba and Yobe. According to a statement by the PDP National Organising Secretary, Col. Austin Akobundu (retd.), on Wednesday,  the party had commenced  membership registration of old and new members. He also said sales of nomination forms, including ad hoc forms, would last till February 22, adding that last day for submission of forms by all aspirants (ward/local government areas/zones and national ex-officials)  would be Saturday, February 29. He said, “Ward congresses to elect ward excos and three ad hoc delegates will be on March 7,  while ward congresses appeal is scheduled for March 12.” He said LGA congresses to elect LGA excos and national delegates would be on March 21, adding that LG congress appeals were for March 25. Copyright PUNCH.
